#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:5
msgid "EGL Support in Emscripten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:7
msgid "This article is under construction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:9
msgid ""
"Khronos Group publishes a specification called EGL, which is an API that "
"handles (among other tasks) graphics context creation, rendering surface "
"management, and interop between different Khronos Group graphics APIs "
"(OpenGL, OpenGL ES, OpenVG). For detailed information, see the `Khronos EGL "
"webpage <http://www.khronos.org/egl>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:11
msgid ""
"Currently, EGL is not very widely used across operating systems/graphics "
"driver vendors. The most notable adoption is in the Android architecture, "
"where EGL is the primary method for creating rendering contexts for OpenGL "
"ES 1&2 when using the Android NDK. Also, Mesa has an implementation of the "
"EGL specification in its `graphics driver <http://www.mesa3d.org/egl.html>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:13
msgid ""
"Emscripten also supplies an implementation of the EGL v1.4 specification. "
"This allows C/C++ client code to use a (nearly) unified codebase for "
"creating a GLES2 (WebGL) rendering context across Web, Linux (with Mesa) and "
"Android NDK. The implementation of the EGL specification in Emscripten is "
"not perfect, see the end of this page for a status chart."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:16
msgid "What EGL is not?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:18
msgid ""
"Somewhat disappointingly, EGL is not a self-sufficient complete solution for "
"initializing GLES2 graphics rendering (on any platform, not just Emscripten) "
"and overseeing various associated tasks. The specification is limited in its "
"scope and lacks some features. In particular, EGL cannot help with the "
"following tasks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:20
msgid ""
"Creating a render window. The EGL specification does not specify how a "
"target window is created to which to render to. One must use platform-"
"specific native window system functions (X11, Win32 API, ANativeWindow) to "
"first create a render window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:21
msgid ""
"Specifying render window size in arbitrary pixel increments. EGL does not "
"have any functionality to request a desired size for the main render window, "
"or to resize it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:22
msgid ""
"Specifying a fullscreen video mode/screen resolution. EGL cannot be used to "
"control whether to render in a windowed or fullscreen mode, or to toggle "
"between these at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:24
msgid ""
"Therefore, for each platform, including Emscripten, there exists platform-"
"specific means to perform these tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:27
msgid "How to create a WebGL context using EGL?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:29
msgid ""
"In the web environment, WebGL is the technology used for 3D-accelerated "
"rendering. WebGL is almost identical to GLES2, and because EGL does not "
"apply at all for WebGL, for all purposes in this page, the terms WebGL and "
"GLES2 are used interchangeably. Therefore to create a WebGL context, one "
"uses EGL, and according to its wording, creates a GLES2 context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:33
msgid "Initialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:35
msgid "Perform the following steps to create a GLES2 context using EGL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:37
msgid ""
"Obtain a handle to an ``EGLDisplay`` object by calling ``eglGetDisplay``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:38
msgid "Initialize EGL on that display by calling ``eglInitialize``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:39
msgid ""
"Call ``eglGetConfigs`` and/or ``eglChooseConfig`` one or multiple times to "
"find the ``EGLConfig`` that represents the desired main render target "
"parameters. To examine the attributes of an ``EGLConfig``, call "
"``eglGetConfigAttrib``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:40
msgid ""
"At this point, one would use whatever platform-specific functions available "
"(*X11*, *Win32 API*, *ANativeWindow*) to set up a native window to render "
"to. For Emscripten, this step does not apply, and can be skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:41
msgid ""
"Create a main render target surface (``EGLSurface``) by calling "
"``eglCreateWindowSurface`` with a valid display and config parameters. Set "
"window and attribute list parameters to null."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:42
msgid ""
"Create a GLES2 rendering context (``EGLContext``) by calling "
"``eglCreateContext``, followed by a call to ``eglMakeCurrent`` to activate "
"the rendering context. When creating the context, specify the context "
"attribute ``EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_VERSION == 2``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:44
msgid ""
"After these steps, you have a set of EGL objects ``EGLDisplay``, "
"``EGLConfig``, ``EGLSurface`` and ``EGLContext`` that represent the main "
"GLES2 rendering context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:47
msgid "Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:49
msgid "The sequence to clean up at de-initialization is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:51
msgid ""
"Free up the currently active rendering context by calling "
"``eglMakeCurrent(display, EGL_NO_SURFACE, EGL_NO_SURFACE, EGL_NO_CONTEXT)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:52
msgid ""
"Deinitialize the ``EGLContext`` object by calling ``eglDestroyContext`` on "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:53
msgid ""
"Destroy all initialized ``EGLSurface`` objects by calling "
"``eglDestroySurface`` on them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:54
msgid "Deinitialize EGL altogether by calling ``eglTerminate(display)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:55
msgid ""
"Delete the native rendering window. This step does not apply for Emscripten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:58
msgid "Sample code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:60
msgid ""
"Example code for using EGL to initialize a WebGL context can be found in the "
"sample applications in the `emscripten/test/third_party/glbook <https://"
"github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/tree/main/test/third_party/glbook>`_ "
"directory, more specifically in the file `esUtil.c <https://github.com/"
"emscripten-core/emscripten/blob/main/test/third_party/glbook/Common/esUtil."
"c>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:63
msgid "Implementation status and notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:65
msgid ""
"This section lists all EGL v1.4 functions and describes their current "
"implementation status in Emscripten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:68
msgid "Fully implemented"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:70
msgid ""
"``eglInitialize``, ``eglGetConfigs``, ``eglQueryContext``, "
"``eglQueryString``, ``eglQuerySurface``, ``eglGetCurrentContext``, "
"``glGetCurrentSurface``, ``eglGetCurrentDisplay``, ``eglReleaseThread``, "
"``eglDestroySurface``, ``eglDestroyContext``: Implemented and should work "
"according to the EGL v1.4 specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:72
msgid ""
"``eglSwapBuffers``: Implemented, but this function cannot really control the "
"swap behavior under WebGL. Calling this function is optional under "
"Emscripten. In WebGL, the contents of the display are always presented to "
"the screen only after the code yields its execution back to the browser, "
"that is, when you return from the tick callback handler you passed to :c:"
"func:`emscripten_set_main_loop`. The ``eglSwapBuffers`` function can however "
"still be used to detect when a GL context loss event occurs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:74
msgid ""
"``eglGetDisplay``: Implemented according to the specification. Emscripten "
"does not utilize multiple ``EGLNativeDisplayType`` objects, so pass in "
"``EGL_DEFAULT_DISPLAY`` here. Emscripten currently actually ignores any "
"value passed in here for Linux emulation purposes, but you should not rely "
"on this in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:76
msgid "``eglGetError``: Implemented according to the specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:78
msgid ""
"According to the specification, ``eglGetError`` reports the single most "
"recent error rather than the list of all previous errors. Don't call this "
"function in a loop in the same way you would call ``glGetError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:82
msgid "Partially implemented"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:84
msgid ""
"``eglChooseConfig``: Implemented as a stub, but this function does not do "
"searching/filtering, and is at the moment identical to ``eglGetConfigs`` "
"(`issue #643 <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues/643>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:86
msgid ""
"``eglGetConfigAttrib``: Implemented. Querying for the attributes "
"``EGL_BUFFER_SIZE``, ``EGL_ALPHA_SIZE``, ``EGL_BLUE_SIZE``, "
"``EGL_GREEN_SIZE``, ``EGL_RED_SIZE``, ``EGL_DEPTH_SIZE`` and "
"``EGL_STENCIL_SIZE`` currently return hardcoded default values (`issue #644 "
"<https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues/644>`_). The "
"attributes ``EGL_MIN_SWAP_INTERVAL`` and ``EGL_MAX_SWAP_INTERVAL`` don't "
"currently have any function. Instead, call :c:func:"
"`emscripten_set_main_loop` to specify the main loop update rate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:88
msgid ""
"``eglCreateWindowSurface``: Implemented, except it is not possible to call "
"this function multiple times to create multiple render windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:90
msgid ""
"``eglCreateContext``: Implemented as a stub. It is not possible to call this "
"function multiple times to create multiple contexts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:92
msgid ""
"``eglBindAPI``, ``eglQueryAPI``: Implemented, although these functions have "
"little utility on Emscripten, since only the GLES2 client API is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:94
msgid ""
"``eglWaitClient``, ``eglWaitNative``: Implemented as no-op functions. These "
"have no meaning on Emscripten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:96
msgid ""
"``eglSwapInterval``: Implemented as a no-op stub. Currently this function "
"cannot set the vsync interval, or enable/disable it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:98
msgid "``eglMakeCurrent``: Implemented as a no-op stub."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:100
msgid ""
"``eglTerminate``: Implemented as a no-op function stub. JavaScript apps are "
"not often shut down manually, but when closing the browser or switching the "
"web page, the browser manages all teardown automatically. Therefore this "
"function does not have a critical importance in Emscripten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:102
msgid "``eglGetProcAddress``: Implemented, experimental."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:105
msgid "Missing functionality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:107
msgid "The following functions are currently not implemented:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:109
msgid ""
"``eglCreatePbufferSurface``, ``eglCreatePixmapSurface``, "
"``eglCreatePbufferFromClientBuffer``, ``eglSurfaceAttrib``, "
"``eglBindTexImage``, ``eglReleaseTexImage``, ``eglWaitGL``, "
"``eglCopyBuffers``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:111
msgid ""
"**Do not call**  these functions in Emscripten code, or the application will "
"halt on trying to execute an undefined function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:114
msgid "EGL extensions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:116
msgid ""
"Currently, Emscripten does not implement any extensions in the `EGL "
"Extension Registry <http://www.khronos.org/registry/egl/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:119
msgid "EGL-related bugs and todos"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/multimedia_and_graphics/EGL-Support-in-Emscripten.rst:121
msgid ""
"The `Emscripten issue tracker <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/"
"issues?labels=EGL&state=open>`_ lists EGL-related issues using the label "
"EGL. Check that page to report or find issues in Emscripten related to EGL."
msgstr ""
